{"atom_id":"ig34_p0271_a025","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":271,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPTESTCD | Parameter Short Name | Char | (PKPARMCD) | Topic | Short name of the pharmacokinetic parameter. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in PPTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., \"1TEST\" is not valid). PPTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: \"AUCALL\", \"TMAX\", \"CMAX\". | Req","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0271_a026","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":271,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPTEST | Parameter Name | Char | (PKPARM) | Synonym Qualifier | Name of the pharmacokinetic parameter. The value in PPTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: \"AUC All\", \"Time of CMAX\", \"Max Conc\". | Req","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0271_a027","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":271,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPCAT | Parameter Category | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a category of related records. For PP, this should be the name of the analyte in PCTEST whose profile the parameter is associated with. | Exp","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0271_a028","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":271,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPSCAT | Parameter Subcategory | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | Categorization of the model type used to calculate the PK parameters. Examples: \"COMPARTMENTAL\", \"NON-COMPARTMENTAL\". | Perm","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0271_a029","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":271,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPORRES | Result or Finding in Original Units | Char | | Result Qualifier | Result of the measurement or finding as originally received or collected. | Exp","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0271_a030","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":271,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPORRESU | Original Units | Char | (PKUNIT) (PKUWG) (PKUWKG) (PKUDMG) (PKUDUG) | Variable Qualifier | Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for PPORRES. Example: \"ng/L\". See PP Assumption 3. | Exp","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPSTRESC | Character Result/Finding in Std Format | Char | | Result Qualifier | Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from PPORRES in a standard format or standard units. PPSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in PPSTRESN. | Exp","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPSTRESN | Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units | Num | | Result Qualifier | Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from PPSTRESC. PPSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings. | Exp","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPSTRESU | Standard Units | Char | (PKUNIT) (PKUWG) (PKUWKG) (PKUDMG) (PKUDUG) | Variable Qualifier | Standardized unit used for PPSTRESC and PPSTRESN. See PP Assumption 3. | Exp","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPSTAT | Completion Status | Char | (ND) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate that a parameter was not calculated. Should be null if a result exists in PPORRES. | Perm","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPREASND | Reason Parameter Not Calculated | Char | | Record Qualifier | Describes why a parameter was not calculated, such as \"INSUFFICIENT DATA\". Used in conjunction with PPSTAT when value is \"NOT DONE\". | Perm","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a006","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPSPEC | Specimen Material Type | Char | (SPECTYPE) | Record Qualifier | Defines the type of specimen used for a measurement. If multiple specimen types are used for a calculation (e.g., serum and urine for renal clearance), then this field should be left blank. Examples: \"SERUM\", \"PLASMA\", \"URINE\". | Exp","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a007","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPANMETH | Analysis Method | Char | (PKANMET) | Record Qualifier | Analysis method applied to obtain a summarized result. Analysis method describes the method of secondary processing applied to a complex observation result. Example: A named formula used to calculate AUC, such as \"LIN-LOG TRAPEZOIDAL METHOD\". Sponsor-defined formulas can also be represented by this variable. Example: Calculating ratio AUCs where the PPANMETH may be \"DRUG METABOLITE 1 TO DRUG PARENT\" or \"DRUG METABOLITE 2 TO METABOLITE 1\". | Perm","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a008","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"TAETORD | Planned Order of Element within Arm | Num | | Timing | Number that gives the planned order of the element within the arm. | Perm","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a009","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"EPOCH | Epoch | Char | (EPOCH) | Timing | Epoch associated with the start date/time of the observation, or the date/time of collection if start date/time is not collected. | Perm","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a010","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPDTC | Date/Time of Parameter Calculations | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Nominal date/time of parameter calculations. | Perm","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a011","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPDY | Study Day of Parameter Calculations | Num | | Timing | Study day of the collection, in integer days. The algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in the Demographics (DM) domain. | Perm","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a012","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPTPTREF | Time Point Reference | Char | | Timing | The description of a time point that acts as a fixed reference for a series of planned time points. | Perm","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a013","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPRFTDTC | Date/Time of Reference Point | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date/time of the reference time point from the PC records used to calculate a parameter record. The values in PPRFTDTC should be the same as that in PCRFTDTC for related records. | Exp","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a014","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PPSTINT | Planned Start of Assessment Interval | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | The start of a planned evaluation or assessment interval relative to the time point reference. | Perm","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
