{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a016","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"NOTE","verbatim":"¹In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a017","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"HEADING","verbatim":"PP – Assumptions","heading_level":6,"sibling_index":3,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a018","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"1. Pharmacokinetics Parameters is a derived dataset, and may be produced from an analysis dataset with a different structure. As a result, some sponsors may need to normalize their analysis dataset in order for it to fit into the SDTM-based PP domain.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a019","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"2. Information pertaining to all parameters (e.g., number of exponents, model weighting) should be submitted in the SUPPPP dataset.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a020","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"3. There are separate codelists used for PPORRESU/PPSTRESU where the choice depends on whether the value of the pharmacokinetic parameter is normalized.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a021","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"a. Codelist \"PKUNIT\" is used for non-normalized parameters.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a022","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"b. Codelists \"PKUDMG\" and \"PKUDUG\" are used when parameters are normalized by dose amount in milligrams or micrograms, respectively.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0272_a023","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":272,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"c. Codelists \"PKUWG\" and \"PKUWKG\" are used when parameters are normalized by weight in grams or kilograms, respectively.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0273_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":273,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"4. Multiple subset codelists were created for the unique unit expressions of the same concept across codelists. This approach allows study-context appropriate use of unit values for pharmacokinetics (PK) analysis subtypes. Controlled Terminology Rules for PK are available at https://www.cdisc.org/standards/terminology/controlled-terminology.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:03:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0273_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":273,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"5. Any Identifiers, Timing variables, or Findings general observation class qualifiers may be added to the PP domain, but the following qualifiers would not generally be used: --BODSYS, --SEV.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:03:00Z"}}
