{"atom_id":"ig34_p0273_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":273,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This example shows PK parameters calculated from time-concentration profiles for the parent drug and 1 metabolite in plasma and urine for one subject. Note that PPRFTDTC is populated in order to link the PP records to the respective PC records. In this example, PPSPEC is null for observed total clearance (PPTESTCD = \"CLO\") records because it is calculated from multiple specimen sources (i.e., plasma and urine).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:03:00Z"}}
